WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.000
US and Japan competition was quite ferocious in major tech sectors, but it really pushed US to improve.

00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:12.000
US to spend a lot more on its innovation system and reform its innovation system.

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:17.000
And in turn, so did Japan, and as a result, we all have cheaper, better products.

00:00:17.000 --> 00:00:26.000
So for investors, at least from what I'm observing, if I were an investor, I think about being in both camps, if I can, to the extent possible.

00:00:26.000 --> 00:00:29.000
Because there'll be some that will be successful in China and the US.

00:00:29.000 --> 00:00:34.000
And you just don't know, you don't know which one, because both have its respective advantages.
